article.story: MURFREESBORO, Tenn. -- — Jestin Porter's 30 points led Middle Tennessee over Jacksonville State 75-67 on Wednesday night. Porter was 10-of-18 shooting, including 4 for 6 from 3-point range, and went 6 for 6 from the line for the Blue Raiders (7-13, 1-4 Conference USA). Elias King scored 23 points and added six rebounds. Jared Jones was 2-of-7 shooting and 4 of 4 from the free-throw line to finish with eight points, while adding eight rebounds and three blocks. Caleb Johnson led the way for the Gamecocks (10-10, 2-3) with 17 points and two steals. Jacksonville State also got 11 points and two steals from KyKy Tandy. In addition, Mason Nicholson had eight points, eight rebounds and three blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
